Ecology and distribution. The single specimen was collected from a small horizontal crevice, with its upper part fully exposed to light. Five ophiuroids are still in place within the bushy part of the sponge. The species is probably rare, as only a single specimen was found in four dives. The area is characterized by warm waters year round, but strong swell may occur when winds blow stronger (August – January,
Silva et al ., 2002
). During this time the abundant sand deposited on top and around the sandstone reefs may be suspended in the water column and increase stress for sponges, which are common occurrences on beach worn debris, at nearby beaches.
